arStrings.szText: “You have all the ingredients. What is next?”

(deep inhale) (sigh) Look at how the sickness has marbled the corpses. This mound’s my best work. The rot here is deep. Like a vibration. A song drownin’ out all others. (sigh) Shame this, silencin’ it forever.
Admiration. He clearly has a deep respect for rot. Zurke is saddened by the last sentence about silencing (killing) the rot here.
I will drive the remedy into the ground. This will stir the swamp. Hold off whatever awakens.
